io.oasp.module.jpa.common.api.to

Class SearchCriteriaTo

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.oasp.module.basic.common.api.to.AbstractTo
      • io.oasp.module.jpa.common.api.to.SearchCriteriaTo
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, net.sf.mmm.util.entity.api.Entity, net.sf.mmm.util.transferobject.api.TransferObject
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    OfferSearchCriteriaTo, OrderPositionSearchCriteriaTo, OrderSearchCriteriaTo, ProductSearchCriteriaTo, StaffMemberSearchCriteriaTo, TableSearchCriteriaTo

    public class SearchCriteriaTo
extends AbstractTo
    This is the interface for a transfer-object with the criteria for a search and pagination query. Such object specifies the criteria selecting which hits will match when performing a search.
    NOTE:
    This interface only holds the necessary settings for the pagination part of a query. For your individual search, you extend SearchCriteriaTo to create a java bean with all the fields for your search.

      • limitMaximumPageSize

        public void limitMaximumPageSize(int limit)
        Limits the page size by the given limit.

        If currently no pagination is active, or the current page size is null or greater than the given limit, the value is replaced by limit

        Parameters:
        limit - is the maximum allowed value for the page size.

      • getSearchTimeout

        public Integer getSearchTimeout()
        This method gets the maximum delay in milliseconds the search may last until it is canceled.
        Note:
        This feature is the same as the query hint "javax.persistence.query.timeout" in JPA.
        Returns:
        the search timeout in milliseconds or null for NO timeout.
